text:
Great Indian food. Their prata is pretty nice, with their fish curry.
Their other dishes, briyani, is a must try. Reasonably priced, no msg used as I do not get thirsty after eating there.

The nasi goreng and Maggie goreng is nice. But lately I went there thrice, each time was inform they are not cooking, only can order prata.

If you don't like passive smoking have to watch out. Alot of smoker congregate here.. smoking aways even though it's non smoking area.

Not really hotel ..a good Mak Mak store I will said ..
Indian -Muslim style so not just the typical Indian serving ..serving 24hrs on the types of nasi goreng , Bryani , prata..
Good alternative in the area beside Khaab Saab at Blk 55 which serve pratas/thosai after 2am to 8am..
Terrible!!!!! We take away the prata. There are overcook till super dark. I don't think the chef dont know. He just ignore. Do business cannot like that. So ugly behavior.

The quality has reduced after the change in chef, from last month. It has also become expensive, you get good food around for lesser price than here.
Also now there is no welcoming service. ðŸ¤”
